On December 17, 1903, the Wright brothers, Orville and Wilbur, achieved the first manned, powered flight in Kitty Hawk, North Carolina. This marked the beginning of aviation and changed history. Wright Brothers Day is a day to commemorate this achievement and look forward to the future of American aviation. The United States has been a leader in aviation innovation, from supersonic jets to space exploration. The aviation industry has transformed the way we live and connect with other nations. The article also mentions that the Trump Administration is working to modernize regulations and fund aerospace research and development to continue America's leadership in aerospace technology. Wright Brothers Day is designated by Congress, and President Trump has issued a proclamation declaring December 17, 2018, as Wright Brothers Day.